data.title: Greenberg Traurig represented Cook Inlet Region, Inc. in acquisitions of ISYS and HABCO Industries. Native corporation CIRI based in Anchorage. OSC Global acquired ISYS.
data.description: In McLean, Virginia on February 26, 2026, the international law firm Greenberg Traurig, LLP assisted Cook Inlet Region, Inc. (CIRI), a Native Alaskan regional corporation in Anchorage, AK, with two acquisitions. One of CIRI's subsidiaries, OSC Global, obtained ISYS in a significant transaction.

data.title: Fosun International recognized for excellence in ESG reporting at HK Management Association awards ceremony on Feb. 23, 2026.
data.description: In Hong Kong, the Hong Kong Management Association (HKMA) organized the 2025 HKMA Best Annual Reports Awards ceremony on February 23, 2026. During the event, Fosun International was honored with the "Certificate of Excellence in Environmental, Social, and Governance." The awards ceremony highlighted achievements in reporting quality and transparency for the year 2025. The event was attended by industry experts, officials, and representatives from numerous organizations.

data.title: Kratos Defense & Security Solutions, Inc. prices public offering of 14.3M shares at $84/share, expecting $1.17B net proceeds.
data.description: Kratos Defense & Security Solutions, Inc. announced the pricing of an underwritten offering of 14,285,714 shares of its common stock on Feb. 26, 2026. The shares were priced at $84.00 each, resulting in expected net proceeds of approximately $1,172,999,977 after deducting underwriting discounts and commissions. The offering was made pursuant to an effective shelf registration statement filed with the SEC. Additionally, Kratos granted the underwriters a 30-day option to purchase up to 2,142,857 additional shares of common stock. All shares in the offering are being sold by Kratos, with the closing expected on March 2, 2026, subject to customary closing conditions.

data.title: Duos Technologies Group, Inc. announces pricing of $65 million public offering of common stock (DUOT).
data.description: Duos Technologies Group, Inc., known as DUOT, has disclosed the pricing of a significant $65 million public offering of their common stock. This move presents a substantial opportunity for investors to acquire ownership in the company.

data.title: Illumination Acquisition Corp I prices $200M IPO of 20M units at $10 each, trading as ILLUU on Nasdaq from Feb 27.
data.description: Illumination Acquisition Corp I has disclosed that it has priced its initial public offering (IPO) of 20,000,000 units at $10.00 per unit. These units will soon be available on the Nasdaq Global Market under the ticker symbol “ILLUU” starting from February 27, 2026. Each unit comprises one Class A ordinary share and one-third of one redeemable warrant. Investors holding a whole warrant will have the right to purchase one Class A ordinary share.

data.title: Generate Biomedicines, Inc. (Nasdaq: GENB) set IPO price on Feb 26, 2026, as a generative biology company utilizing AI.
data.description: Generate Biomedicines, Inc., a company based in Somerville, Massachusetts, revealed on February 26, 2026, that it has priced its initial public offering. Trading under the ticker symbol GENB on the Nasdaq exchange, Generate is known for its work in generative biology and AI applications in biotechnology and drug development. The announcement marks a significant step for the clinical-stage company as it enters the public market.
